editorialSummary.text: Classic, long-running fast-food chain known for its burgers & fries.

text.text:
Extremely disappointed in the new menu Yakiniku burger. I ordered the chicken version and it turned out super soggy and dry... i ordered from drive thru and immediately ate it (within 5 mins)

Poster look nothing like the one i received. When i open the packaging, it jus looks depressing.

The Patty is super dry and is so damn soggy, no crunch at all even at the side.

Bread is hard and dry, not fluffy and soft ....

Veggies are old hence the dark color.

Feels like a pre-prepped burger and just pop it in to the bag

Overall a very sad experience and disappointed as since im a student, spending $10 for this meal is not worth.

text.text:
This visit was extra pleasant. I was eating by myself. And had chosen to pay by cash, so table service was not an option. So I waited for my food at the counter, but the manager told me to take a seat and that he will bring my food to me. I am 8 months pregnant. So I think that was extremely kind of him. I really appreciated the gesture. He even got me both chili sauce and ketchup. Very thoughtful.
Shout out to the manager that day.

text.text: Always wonder will reviews be taken seriously by owner or just helping customers to make informed decisions. Ordered my meal on McDonald's App and very disappointed with the lousy french fries that was short, salty and totally stale like left there for a long time, asked specifically for BBQ sauce for chicken nuggets and when I got home, curry sauce was given. There is no excuse as the order was clearly stated in receipt not verbally. The restaurant was not busy when I picked up the food but yet substandard food was served is really unacceptable.  First time I am disappointed with McDonald's. Hope there will be vast improvement.

text.text:
This is a big open air food center that serves a variety of local food  at heartland prices. The place generally serves the morning and afternoon crowd, but there are still a number of stalls open in the evening. The place starts to wind down around 8-9 pm.

Besides the food center is the  wet market that opens in the morning. In between the wet market and food centre are rows of small shop units selling different wares from Chinese Tea to clothing and kitchen ware.

text.text: Takagi has been going from good to bad and now worse. Ordered their chili crab ramen for $16 which was pretty expensive considering the small bowl portion! Taste was bland and the crab has a fishy weird smell. The only good thing was the broth, but the service is way too slow and ridiculous especially that the stall did not have full house when I visited. Overall 1/5 experience for me as compared to the old days, really disappointing and expensive to me! Do not recommend in my opinion.

text.text: Affordable and yummy ramen! Added egg for $1.50 if I’m not wrong. Broth was great, I drank all the soup. The space is a bit narrow and cramped though as the shop wanted to provide the authentic experience of eating in Japanese eateries. The waiting time is quite long during weekday lunch sadly. I think it was almost 30 minutes from ordering to getting our food. I’d still return there next time!

text.text: Always enjoy a good meal here at Takagi Ramen! Generous servings with flavourful sauces and broth. Prices are kept affordable too with no GST and service charge.

originalText.text: Always enjoy a good meal here at Takagi Ramen! Generous servings with flavourful sauces and broth. Prices are kept affordable too with no GST and service charge.

text.text:
Had my supper after midnight to read manhwa and enjoy a Takagi Ramen bowl of tonkotsu broth, 2 slices of chashu, spring onions, and bean sprouts (with added seaweed and egg); Chicken Karaage with a side of chopped lettuce, and mayonnaise; and a large cup of Shio Collagen Kuriimu Oolong Milk Tea with Grass Jelly.

To commemorate the onset of summer, I had the Matsuri specialty dessert Uji Matcha and Yoshino Sakura Mochi snack boxes, pre-sweetened silky glutinous rice cakes to take home and enjoy. Pairs well with hot green tea.

text.text:
KFC is KFC, nothing spectacular, just a normal fast food chain. Decent fried chicken, standard taste if you've had it before.

Just to note that this review is specifically for this outlet. The service can sometimes be horribly slow. Even when you order in advance through the app and give it a good 20 minutes before coming, high chance that you'll still be waiting. Also do check your orders if you have take-out as few times I've had my order wrong before. Other than that, the place is nice if you're dining in.
